{"word":"男の人","reading":"おとこのひと","meaning":"man","pos":"noun","example":"あの男の人はだれですか。","exampleReading":"あのおとこのひとはだれですか。","exampleMeaning":"Who is that man?","tip":"Bare 男 can sound blunt — 男の人 is the polite everyday way to say 'man'."},
{"word":"女の人","reading":"おんなのひと","meaning":"woman","pos":"noun","example":"女の人が歌っている。","exampleReading":"おんなのひとがうたっている。","exampleMeaning":"A woman is singing.","tip":"Politer than bare 女. Even politer: 女性 (じょせい)."},
{"word":"母","reading":"はは","meaning":"(my) mother","pos":"noun","example":"母は先生です。","exampleReading":"はははせんせいです。","exampleMeaning":"My mother is a teacher.","tip":"はは for YOUR own mother when talking to others; someone else's is お母さん."},
{"word":"父","reading":"ちち","meaning":"(my) father","pos":"noun","example":"父は今、仕事です。","exampleReading":"ちちはいま、しごとです。","exampleMeaning":"My father is at work now.","tip":"ちち for your own father; others' fathers (and calling out to yours) is お父さん."},
{"word":"食べ物","reading":"たべもの","meaning":"food","pos":"noun","example":"好きな食べ物は何ですか。","exampleReading":"すきなたべものはなんですか。","exampleMeaning":"What's your favorite food?","tip":"物 (thing) builds nouns from verbs: 食べ物 eat-thing, 飲み物 drink-thing, 買い物 shopping."},
{"word":"飲み物","reading":"のみもの","meaning":"drink, beverage","pos":"noun","example":"飲み物は何にしますか。","exampleReading":"のみものはなんにしますか。","exampleMeaning":"What will you have to drink?"},
{"word":"ご飯","reading":"ごはん","meaning":"rice, meal","pos":"noun","example":"ご飯を食べましたか。","exampleReading":"ごはんをたべましたか。","exampleMeaning":"Have you eaten?","tip":"Means both cooked rice and 'meal': 朝ご飯 breakfast, 昼ご飯 lunch, 晩ご飯 dinner."},
{"word":"週末","reading":"しゅうまつ","meaning":"weekend","pos":"noun","example":"週末は何をしますか。","exampleReading":"しゅうまつはなにをしますか。","exampleMeaning":"What are you doing this weekend?"},
{"word":"今週","reading":"こんしゅう","meaning":"this week","pos":"noun","example":"今週は忙しい。","exampleReading":"こんしゅうはいそがしい。","exampleMeaning":"This week is busy.","tip":"The pattern: 今週 this / 来週 next / 先週 last week. Same with 月 and 年."},
{"word":"来週","reading":"らいしゅう","meaning":"next week","pos":"noun","example":"来週、テストがある。","exampleReading":"らいしゅう、テストがある。","exampleMeaning":"There's a test next week."},
{"word":"去年","reading":"きょねん","meaning":"last year","pos":"noun","example":"去年、日本に行った。","exampleReading":"きょねん、にほんにいった。","exampleMeaning":"I went to Japan last year.","tip":"Irregular: last year is きょねん but last week is 先週 — no 去週 exists."},
{"word":"走る","reading":"はしる","meaning":"to run","pos":"verb","example":"駅まで走った。","exampleReading":"えきまではしった。","exampleMeaning":"I ran to the station.","tip":"Godan despite the る: 走ります, 走らない."},
{"word":"泳ぐ","reading":"およぐ","meaning":"to swim","pos":"verb","example":"海で泳ぐのが好きだ。","exampleReading":"うみでおよぐのがすきだ。","exampleMeaning":"I like swimming in the sea."},
{"word":"歩く","reading":"あるく","meaning":"to walk","pos":"verb","example":"毎日、駅まで歩く。","exampleReading":"まいにち、えきまであるく。","exampleMeaning":"I walk to the station every day."},
{"word":"座る","reading":"すわる","meaning":"to sit","pos":"verb","example":"どうぞ、座ってください。","exampleReading":"どうぞ、すわってください。","exampleMeaning":"Please, have a seat.","tip":"Godan: 座ります. どうぞ + 座ってください is how you offer someone a chair."},
{"word":"教える","reading":"おしえる","meaning":"to teach, to tell","pos":"verb","example":"メールを教えてください。","exampleReading":"メールをおしえてください。","exampleMeaning":"Please tell me your email.","tip":"Covers 'teach' AND 'tell/share info' — asking directions is 道を教えてください."},
{"word":"覚える","reading":"おぼえる","meaning":"to memorize, to learn","pos":"verb","example":"漢字を十個覚えた。","exampleReading":"かんじをじゅっこおぼえた。","exampleMeaning":"I memorized ten kanji.","tip":"'I remember it' (the state) is 覚えている."},
{"word":"忘れる","reading":"わすれる","meaning":"to forget","pos":"verb","example":"名前を忘れました。","exampleReading":"なまえをわすれました。","exampleMeaning":"I forgot the name.","tip":"Also 'leave behind': かさを忘れた — I forgot (left) my umbrella."},
{"word":"始まる","reading":"はじまる","meaning":"to begin","pos":"verb","example":"映画は七時に始まる。","exampleReading":"えいがはしちじにはじまる。","exampleMeaning":"The movie starts at seven.","tip":"Intransitive — things start by themselves. YOU start something with 始める."},
{"word":"終わる","reading":"おわる","meaning":"to end, to finish","pos":"verb","example":"仕事は六時に終わる。","exampleReading":"しごとはろくじにおわる。","exampleMeaning":"Work ends at six."},
{"word":"疲れる","reading":"つかれる","meaning":"to get tired","pos":"verb","example":"今日は疲れた。","exampleReading":"きょうはつかれた。","exampleMeaning":"I'm tired today.","tip":"'I'm tired' is past tense 疲れた — the getting-tired already happened."},
{"word":"病気","reading":"びょうき","meaning":"illness, sick","pos":"noun","example":"病気で学校を休んだ。","exampleReading":"びょうきでがっこうをやすんだ。","exampleMeaning":"I missed school because I was sick."},
{"word":"薬","reading":"くすり","meaning":"medicine","pos":"noun","example":"薬を飲んでください。","exampleReading":"くすりをのんでください。","exampleMeaning":"Please take the medicine.","tip":"Medicine is 'drunk' in Japanese — 薬を飲む — even when it's pills."},
{"word":"痛い","reading":"いたい","meaning":"painful, ouch","pos":"adjective","example":"頭が痛いです。","exampleReading":"あたまがいたいです。","exampleMeaning":"My head hurts.","tip":"Body part + が + 痛い covers every ache. Shouted alone, いたい！ = 'ouch!'"},
{"word":"休み","reading":"やすみ","meaning":"day off, break","pos":"noun","example":"明日は休みです。","exampleReading":"あしたはやすみです。","exampleMeaning":"Tomorrow is my day off.","tip":"The noun of 休む: lunch break is 昼休み, summer vacation is 夏休み."}
]
